description: With many questions left unanswered, Yoshimori and Tokine escape Headless Island. All is peaceful back home at the Karasumori Site...until a mysterious fissure cracks open the school grounds. Then Mt. Okubi, the largest of the mystical sites, is attacked, and its enraged guardian deity goes on a rampage! The Shadow Organization sends a powerful, polite young man to help guard Karasumori--but can he be trusted? And who needs help anyway?!
name: Vol. 23

description: The 1960s adventures of J'onn J'onzz are collected in this new volume featuring stories from DETECTIVE COMICS #305-326 and HOUSE OF MYSTERY #143-173!
name: Volume 2

description:
Mikito Sakurai is tired of being a punching bag for all the delinquents on campus. But what can he do? By nature he's a gentle and easygoing high school student. That all changes the night he swallows a mysterious orb and meets Zakuro, a strange kid who promises to grant his most heartfelt desire. "When you wake up," says the pint-sized apparition, "you'll be stronger and better than a human."

And that's exactly what happens. Mikito wakes up with superstrength. But there's a catch. He may look the same on the outside, but deep inside lurks a monster that craves ultraviolence and the taste of human flesh. "I used to hate the sight of blood," says Mikito to himself, "but now it looks so beautiful to me."
name: Vol. 1

description: A couple of ogre hunters have discovered Mikito's dark secret. Instead of being killed, however, Mikito is enlisted in a hunt to track down wild gangs of monsters. Hopefully, when the hunt is over, Mikito can find a way to stay alive!
name: Vol. 2

description: Some of the greatest Batman tales ever are collected in this new hardcover! Reprinting the classic BATMAN ANNUALs #1-3 from 1961 and 1962, this can't-miss collection reveals the secrets of the Batcave, the Bat-Signal and more!
name: Volume One

volume.name: DC Comics Classics Library: Batman - The Annuals

description:
Jon of Gallund likes nothing better than fighting and carousing, but when his father, Jarl Rollo, arranges his marriage to the princess of another tribe, he must undertake a dangerous quest into the frozen north!
 
The paperback edition is identical to the hardcover version, except for the cover art. 
 
Introduction written by Will Eisner
name: Paperback

description:
Jon of Gallund likes nothing better than fighting and carousing, but when his father, Jarl Rollo, arranges his marriage to the princess of another tribe, he must undertake a dangerous quest into the frozen north!
 
The paperback edition is identical to the hardcover version, except for the cover art.
 
 This is the hardcover edition.
name: Hardcover

description: Batman's 80-Page Giant Annuals issues #4-7 are collected in this volume including "The Secret Marriage of Batman and Batwoman," "The Phantom of the Batcave," "The First Batman," plus appearances by Giant Batman, Rip Van Batman, Zebra Batman, Merman Batman and more.
name: Volume Two

volume.name: DC Comics Classics Library: Batman - The Annuals

description:
Ando's desperate attempt to prevent a gas station explosion will bring him face-to-face with Inukai. But will their confrontation only spur on Ando's decision to fight, or will new challenges be too much for him to bear...?

  • Chapter 18: Now Is That Time
  • Chapter 19: The Power of A Word
  • Chapter 20: The Wrong World and the Right World
  • Chapter 21: God's Recipe
  • Chapter 22: At Your Doorstep
  • Chapter 23: Premonitions
  • Chapter 24: The Meaning of Life
  • Chapter 25: Flight
  • Chapter 26: The Crossroads of Fate
  • Chapter 27: Long Dark Night
name: Vol. 3

description:
As Inukai reveals his dark ambitions for the city, Ando is more determined than ever to fight back in any way he can. But when he discovers that his power comes with a painful side effect, how will he respond?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 28: Lights of Solidarity
  • Chapter 29: Target
  • Chapter 30: Inukai's Light and Ando's Isolation
  • Chapter 31: The Scars of A Single Night
  • Chapter 32: Encounter
  • Chapter 33: Cry of the Bystander
  • Chapter 34: Resignation and Conspiracy
  • Chapter 35: Breaking Point
  • Chapter 36: Dead End
  • Chapter 37: The Future Before My Eyes
name: Vol. 4

description:
As a child Sakura Mamiya mysteriously disappeared in the woods behind her grandma's home. She returned whole and healthy, but since then she has had the power to see ghosts. Now a teenager, she just wishes the ghosts would leave her alone! At school, the desk next to Sakura's has been empty since the start of the school year. Then one day her always-absent classmate Rinne Rokudo shows up, and he's far more than what he seems!

Death can be a laughing matter!

Sakura's curiosity about the mysterious Rinne draws her deeper into an amazing world on the boundary between the living and the dead. Helping Rinne is one thing, but will tagging along with him leave her trapped in the afterlife? And does Rinne really know what he's doing? Dealing with the afterlife isn't easy, especially when you don't know all the rules!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: The Mysterious Classmate
  • Chapter 2: The Legend of the Weather Hutch
  • Chapter 3: Four O'Clock Behind the Gym
  • Chapter 4: Have We Met?
  • Chapter 5: Y-O-U-N-G Woman
  • Chapter 6: Mystery In the Club Building
  • Chapter 7: Black Cat By Contract
  • Chapter 8: Afraid To Fall Asleep
name: Vol. 1

description: Sakura and Rinne deal with the ghosts of an ancient warrior and a girl who drowned in the school swimming pool, but that's just a warm-up! A wandering spirit leads them to a surprising confrontation, one that takes Sakura and Rinne on an even more amazing chase!
name: Vol. 2

description:
A boy from Sakura's past appears, hoping to win a date with her. But the ghost of another lovelorn boy leads to an unexpected triple date. Can an exorcism take place at an amusement park? Does Rinne have feelings for Sakura? Compared to playing the dating game, dealing with angry ghosts and rogue shinigami may be less frightening!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 19: The Transfer Student
  • Chapter 20: If You Don't Mind, Let's Be Friends First
  • Chapter 21: A Fun Date
  • Chapter 22: One Hundred Thousand Yen
  • Chapter 23: The Price of Power
  • Chapter 24: Shinigami Scythe
  • Chapter 25: Lure of the Pumpkinhead
  • Chapter 26: Hall of the Damashigami
  • Chapter 27: Draw Me
  • Chapter 28: Black & White
name: Vol. 3

description: While suffering from a cold, Rinne gets a visit from a very strange doctor. The surprise house call leads Rinne, Sakura and Tsubasa to a confrontation with Sabato, Rinne's deadbeat father and president of the evil Damashigami Company! The stage is set for an all-out father-son battle in the afterlife.
name: Vol. 4

description:
As Azuma and Team Pantasia compete in the eleventh round of the "Yakitate!! 25" bread battle, they realize that a reaction to an eggy creation has transformed judge Kuro-yan into Pantasia's archenemy, Kirisaki! Azuma tries buttering him up to roll back the team's imminent defeat, but in the process a shocking truth about their shared history is revealed! A rare type of flour just may soothe the wounds of the past--but will going against the grain help Azuma and his team or just cause more bitter feelings?

Chapter Titles

  • Story 213: If the Game Lasts Until the Bottom of the Ninth, How Many Times Would You Jump?
  • Story 214: The Second Handshake
  • Story 215: Kirisaki and the Bread
  • Story 216: Just Another Geezer
  • Story 217: Looking for the Old Man
  • Story 218: Umajiro's Hope
  • Story 219: A Most Serious Match
  • Story 220: The muscle Strength of a Magician
  • Story 221: Kawachi's Training
  • Story 222: Bread-Making Form
name: Vol. 24

description:
Azuma and his long-time bread battle partner Kawachi must compete with one another in order to obtain a magical grain called "Dharma." Though he's played the fool all along, Kawachi picks up a handy skill that just might give his creation the edge over his old friend's dutiful dough. Later, the team's former rival Kirisaki cooks up a plan to control the world through his sinfully delicious bread. The fate of the universe hangs in the balance as Azuma works tirelessly to perfect the recipe for his ultimate--and potentially universe-saving--Ja-pan!

Chapter Titles

  • Story 223: Azuma's Love
  • Story 224: Two Ingredients
  • Story 225: The Most Beautiful Thing
  • Story 226: Meister's Desperation
  • Story 227: Of Bread and Men
  • Story 228: Messed-Up Kawachi
  • Story 229: Final Form
  • Story 230: Azuma's Lie
  • Story 231: Kuroyanagi and His King
  • Yakitate!! Japan Bonus Story: Super H!! Tsukino Azusagawa
name: Vol. 25

description:
The New Captain America comes face-to-face with an old ally – Prince Namor – on a dangerous trip to China. Can Bucky and Namor team-up to save the memory of an old comrade-in-arms as Cold War crimes come back to haunt the Winter Soldier?!!

Also, has Tony Stark come face to face with his equal? His better? Stark Industries is beset on all sides by the evil Ezekiel Stane and his hordes of suicide bombers around the world. Can Iron Man be in four places at once while his empire crumbles? Don’t miss the devastating conclusion to The Five Nightmares!

It's Bucky versus Batroc and a mysterious foreign agent from his past as the Winter Soldier, as he fights to keep a secret super-weapon from falling into enemy hands! But the shocking ending of this tale brings a new twist to the mission... and sends our New Captain America in search of whatever is left of his old comrades, the Invaders!

Plus, Loki’s machinations have born their darkest fruit as Thor begins his exile. Meanwhile, Balder, Lord of the Eternal Realm, makes a startling decision that will affect the lives of all his people!

Includes material reprinted from Invincible Iron Man #6, Captain America #46 and Thor #600!
name: The Submariner Strikes Back!

description: Disguised as Zero, Lelouch uses the power of Geass to turn the tables on The Brittania Empire. But how far will he go to achieve his dreams of revolution?
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Code Geass: Lelouch of the Rebellion

description:
Paifu, a half-vampire half-werekoala, is always getting into trouble with his best buddy, José the ghost. But when the Monster Flu sweeps through town, the fun and games are over. If the monsters don't get the medicine soon, everyone will die! With all the adults sick, it's up to the kids to save the day!

Paifu and José are off on a big adventure, but will they get the medicine in time...or will they become victims themselves?!

  • Fright 1: Paifu Goes on an Errand
  • Fright 2: The Unhaunted House
  • Fright 3: Paifu and Arpon
  • Fright 4: Monster Flu
  • Fright 5: Off to Horned-Owl Mountain
  • Fright 6: Mako "The Murderer" Maruyama
  • Fright 7: The Road Goes On

  • Fright 14: Makoleen's Boat

description: The battle between Creed's Apostles and the Cerberus Team ends in a draw, with serious wounds on both sides. Just when Train thinks he can relax again, his friends Sven and Eve are captured by Creed, who believes that killing them is the only way to get Train to join him. Now Train has to race to save the only people he can trust.
name: Big Changes

description:
The Chronos assault team Cerberus discovers the location of Creed's hideout and finally confronts him, only to find themselves battling a beast created by nanomachine technology. Sensing danger, Train appears on the scene. But instead of taking sides, Train has his own agenda.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 76: The Werewolf
  • Chapter 77: Nanotech Power
  • Chapter 78: Transcendent Power
  • Chapter 79: Showdown at the Old Castle
  • Chapter 80: Escape
  • Chapter 81: Imagine Blade, Level 2
  • Chapter 82: Nizer's Resolve
  • Chapter 83: The Way of the Numbers
  • Chapter 84: No. X, Shaolee
name: Showdown at the Old Castle

description:
With her fate lying in Sephiria's manipulative hands, Rinslet becomes a pawn in the Cerberus commando team's search for Creed and their ongoing attempt to destroy the Apostles of the Star. Meanwhile, a stranger sends Train, Sven and Eve on a mission to find a missing person they may already know all too well.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 68: Days of Youth
  • Chapter 69: Rinslet's Ordeal
  • Chapter 70: Cerberus
  • Chapter 71: The Mission Commences
  • Chapter 72: Cerberus Strikes
  • Chapter 73: The Apostles' Vicious Assault
  • Chapter 74: Enter Train
  • Chapter 75: Train Approaches
  • Bonus Story: Stray Cat
name: Cerberus Strikes

description: The character focus of Essex County shifts from Lester Paineau to elderly Lou Lebeuf; decrepit and senile, Lou's story is told through a series of flashbacks to his days playing for a semi=professional Toronto hockey team. Along with his brother Vince, Lou finds success on the ice; however, not everything between these two siblings is as amorous as it seems. Interspersed with these events is Lou's interactions with his nurse, Anne. it serves as a reflection of getting old, and regretting mistakes that have taken far too long to be realized.
name: Vol. 2: Ghost Stories

description: "The Country Nurse" concludes the Essex County trilogy by switching the character focus yet again to Anne, Lou's nurse from the previous book. Through her, we get to experience the middle-age of life, caring for others and trying to remain a good person. Featured heavily are tie-ups of previous plot threads: Lemire delves deeper into the threads of infidelity and lies that run through Essex County, all while giving us a look into the history that has shaped the region. A great finish to the series.
name: Vol. 3: The Country Nurse

description: Sena faces a brick wall in the form of hulking über-athlete, Shin, of the White Knights. Rather than run away, Sena runs at full speed, straight at this exciting new challenge! But will Sena's frail body hold up to all the brain-jostling tackles that Shin dishes out?
name: And They're Called The Devil Bats

description: The Devil Bats face off against the Chamelons--a team of ruthless delinquents. But when fragile Sena goes up against the Chameleon's sinister ace linebacker, who will be intimidating whom?
name: Intimidation

description: The Devil Bats finagle their way into a game against the behemoth-like Taiyo Sphinx. The winners will get a chance to scrimmage against a high school championship team in the United States. Will Sena and crew be able to break down the Sphinx's invincible "pyramid" front line and send them crying home to their mummies?

The Devil Bats are going to feel like dancing for joy if they can beat Banba and his hulking team, the Taiyo Sphinx. And don't forget, the winner of this game gets to play against a championship team from the United States!

And later, Sena and Monta search for a much-needed kicker to join the team and find him in a most unexpected place.

description: The Devil Bats take on the NASA Aliens! After months of grueling training, the game against the Americans is finally about to begin. But the Aliens have a huge front line and a quarterback with an arm like a rocket launcher. Will the Devil Bats be able to clinch the win before the Aliens' score goes up into orbit?!

Before she knows what's happening to her, Haru is drawn into a world inhabited entirely by talking cats--and recruited to be the next Cat Princess! Only the dapper cat Baron and his friends, a magical crow and a comical fat cat, along with a friend from Haru's past, can help her return home.
